      • unparseableExpression

        public void unparseableExpression(Exception parseException,
                         String exprName)
        Description copied from interface: DuzztDiagnosticListener
        Called if an expression could not be parsed.

        If the parse error occurred while parsing a named subexpression, the name of the subexpression will also be passed as the exprName parameter. Otherwise (that is, if the main expression could not be parsed), exprName will be null.

        Specified by:
        unparseableExpression in interface DuzztDiagnosticListener
        Parameters:
        parseException - the exception that was thrown while trying to parse
        exprName - the name of the named subexpression, or null if the parse error occurred while parsing the main expression.
